      "author": "jv209",
      "description": "Fixes settings-page color swatches rendering black on Obsidian 1.13+.\n\nThe v1.6.4 fix made every setter of `--callout-color` emit a full CSS color (`rgb(...)`) on Obsidian 1.13+, but the plugin stylesheet still consumed it as `rgb(var(--callout-color))`, which expanded to `rgb(rgb(r, g, b))` — invalid CSS — so swatch icons on the Detection and Custom Callouts settings tabs (and the insert / quick-pick previews) fell back to black. The editor was unaffected.\n\nThe swatch CSS now reads `--callout-color` directly, and the four swatch sites emit an always-valid color via a new `formatSwatchColor()` helper. The live-preview callout in the edit modal keeps the version-gated `formatCalloutColor()`.",
      "downloadCount": 4,
      "draft": false,
      "name": "1.6.10",
      "prerelease": false,
