      "author": "jv209",
      "description": "Fixes custom callout colors being blanked on **Obsidian 1.13+**.\n\nObsidian 1.13.0 changed `--callout-color` to require a valid CSS color instead of a bare RGB triplet. Callouts you create in the plugin now emit `rgb(...)` on 1.13+ and the legacy triplet on older Obsidian, so colors render correctly on both. `minAppVersion` is unchanged — nothing breaks for users on older builds.\n\n**Using hand-written CSS snippets?** Wrap their colors in `rgb()` (e.g. `--callout-color: rgb(68, 138, 255);`) to fix them on 1.13+. See the README note for details.",
